== Calendar? ==

Were Gregorian and Julian calendar really a year apart in those days, or are the death date years given in this article simply a mistake? --[[User:WolfD59|WolfD59]] ([[User talk:WolfD59|talk]]) 10:27, 31 May 2016 (UTC)

:The new year began on March 25 in the Julian calendar.  As a result, dates between January 1 and March 25 fall in the year before that of the Gregorian calendar. ''[[User:Magicpiano|<span style="background-color:khaki;color:firebrick;">Magic</span>]]''[[User_talk:Magicpiano|â™ªpiano]] 12:10, 31 May 2016 (UTC)
